However, social media should not be treated as a complete or reliable news source.

If it is safe to inform others about {{project_name_short}}, users can [[Contribute|Contribute]] by sharing official news through an anonymous account.

This page can be shared on: {{Share}}
}} <!-- close tab -->

{{Tab
|title= == Source Code ==
|content=
Users interested in {{project_name_short}} source code updates can [[Dev/git#subscribe_to_code_changes|subscribe to code changes]].

Source code updates are for users who want to follow development at the code level. They are not a replacement for Important News or All News.
}} <!-- close tab -->

}} <!-- close tab controller -->

= Reason =

Security and software issues sometimes require quick action from users. For example, users may need to update immediately, avoid a broken update, or temporarily stop using a feature until a fix is available.

Following official {{project_name_short}} news helps users receive these warnings in time.

= Debian Security Announcements =

Since {{project_name_short}} is [[Based_on_Debian|based on Debian]], users should consider subscribing to the Debian [https://lists.debian.org/debian-security-announce/ security announcement mailing list] to stay informed about Debian security advisories.

See also: [[Operating_System_Hardening#Debian_Security_Announcements|Debian Security Announcements]].

= Operating System Updates =

It is important to regularly check for [[Operating_System_Software_and_Updates#Updates|operating system updates]] on the host operating system and all {{VMs}}.

= Running systemcheck =

See {{kicksecure_wiki
|wikipage=systemcheck
|text=systemcheck
}}.

